 {"id":"franken_numpy-3c84","title":"Return NaN matrices for non-finite expm/sqrtm inputs","description":"`expm_nxn` and `sqrtm_nxn` currently fail closed on any non-finite input, but SciPy returns all-NaN matrices for these cases. `logm_nxn` still raises, so only expm/sqrtm should change.\n\nEvidence:\n- `scipy.linalg.expm([[inf,1],[2,3]]) -> [[nan,nan],[nan,nan]]`\n- `scipy.linalg.sqrtm([[nan,1],[2,3]]) -> [[nan,nan],[nan,nan]]`\n\nGoal: preserve current `logm_nxn` error behavior, but make `expm_nxn` and `sqrtm_nxn` return all-NaN outputs on non-finite input with regression tests.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:56:04.743192328Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-01T19:07:11.426817227Z","closed_at":"2026-04-01T19:07:11.426511508Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
